Subject: Request for CVE Identifier: bzexe insecure temporary file

This is a security issue reported by vladz in bzexe. This is a low impact security issue, since bzexe is rarely used and the race condition window is very narrow, but still exploitable.

http://lists.grok.org.uk/pipermail/full-disclosure/2011-October/083701.html
http://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=632862

Can a CVE Identifier be assigned to this issue?

